article.headline: Northwestern 78, Purdue 76 (OT)
article.story: WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. (AP) -- Vedran Vukusic scored eight of his 29 points in overtime to lead Northwestern to a 78-76 win over Purdue on Wednesday night. Vukusic shot 12-of-19, including 4-of-10 on 3-pointers. Mohamed Hachad added 20 points on 4-of-5 3-point shooting for the Wildcats (10-8, 3-4 Big Ten). Marcus White, Bryant Dillon and Matt Kiefer each scored 18 points for the Boilermakers (7-11, 1-6). Dillon hit a 3-pointer from the right corner with 11.8 seconds left in regulation and time running out on the shot clock to give the Boilermakers a 66-63 lead. Northwestern's Craig Moore then came off a screen and hit a contested 3-pointer from the right wing with 0.9 seconds left to force overtime. Purdue led 23-18 in the first half before the Wildcats hit four 3-pointers, including two by Hachad, to take a 30-28 halftime lead. Hachad had 13 points at the break, better than his average of 10 points per game. The Boilermakers outrebounded the Wildcats 17-5 and shot 50 percent from the field in the first half, but still trailed at halftime because of 10 turnovers and poor defense. Northwestern hit 12-of-29 3-pointers overall. Purdue outrebounded the Wildcats 33-15 and shot 57 percent from the field.
